President Biden has declared a state of emergency in Guam due to the conditions caused by Typhoon Mawar. This declaration authorizes the Department of Homeland Security, specifically the Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA), to coordinate disaster relief efforts and provide assistance to alleviate the hardship and suffering caused by the emergency. FEMA is authorized to mobilize equipment and resources as needed to mitigate the impacts of the emergency. Under the Public Assistance program, limited direct federal assistance will be provided at 75 percent federal funding. Benigno B. Ruiz of FEMA has been appointed to coordinate federal recovery operations in the affected areas. For more information, the media can contact the FEMA news desk.